title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1979-09-05
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half-Step > Franklin's Tower, Mama Tried  > Mexicali Blues, Peggy O., Cassidy,  Loser,  The Promised Land

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias  > Fire on the Mountain, Estimated Prophet  > Eyes of the World > Drums > Space > Black Peter, I Need a Miracle > Bertha > Good Lovin' ; Encore: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: That nice Cassette tape Feeling Hits you instantly. The Cassette-ness. Now to listen to this thing.

Good Show. Beautiful Matrix. I was taken by surprise by this show while traveling, listening to my iPod. Hunter does a beautiful job on this matrix, though I've added a goodly amount of reverb to soften up the sterile board.  Jerry is still a month away from ditching his laryngitis completely (wobbling and warbling through Half Step et al).  And even with the Half Step being off a bit vocally, I just adore it and Franklin's Tower - especially the Tower!  If you have music editing software, Eyes needs to be slowed down.  Its definitely fixable and very good when you can. 

This is a slightly flawed, but solid four star show overall - with a smokin' finish! With the very high energy Miracle > Bertha > Good Lovin', U.S. Blues ending which I see only a few times a year, I'm adding another half a star to get to 4.5.  And with Hunter’s magic, I'm bumping that up to five.  Hey, whatever it takes to get there!  Thanks Hunter.
I'll show you! @lilrichwhiteboy - I can show you exactly where Ben Franklin's Tower is here in Philadelphia at 4th St. & Arch St.
